The paper discusses coding schemes for random projections, which are commonly used in machine learning and information retrieval. This makes it likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions an application to computer vision (cs.CV) and training support vector machines (cs.AI), which further supports these sub-categories as likely choices.
